<treatment id="E65976F77E8A5D4D9A095D3B236FA8EC" ID-GBIF-Taxon="194317849" LSID="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:04EA59DC-C5AD-486B-A3CB-AA7076F5ABE5" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/E65976F77E8A5D4D9A095D3B236FA8EC" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<subSubSection id="4DE80B56FC8CE4484C778CB66327EB49" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="F8A6ECC9A174DDC016EE4064E4685320" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="BE29AB51B49975E7CA70E1606348E8F7" LSID="http://zoobank.org/04EA59DC-C5AD-486B-A3CB-AA7076F5ABE5" authority="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui, 2022" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Deltanthura</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EEDB9A5162DB1E1A391A87B85C10DB2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BE3F81BCEAAE078CED80C36FEE8F2AFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="135D0F622D0B40B9B19103E703FAC499" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3165B965F429E67EBE16E58CECEC00D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Eyes present. Pereonite 7 reduced and hidden laterally. Pleonites 1-5 fused but with sutures. Pleonite 6 entirely fused dorsally to telson; pleotelson triangular, without statocyst. Mandible acute, with 3-articulate palp. Maxilliped with 4-articulate palp; endite present. Pereopod 7 absent on non-manca individuals. Uropodal exopod elongate triangular, tapering.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="857CDE6F6975AA55AD7D16F6C725FC2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="type species">
<paragraph id="B4F2FE71D427329EB367765E65B0FD45" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7BFF6EA8E767567551B639CDC804CCE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="B8F4474F7F10735BE8EE21EFB9BE188B" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura palpus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="palpus">
<emphasis id="E60F11A88C69E6BB534A4B573099D23E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura palpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Shiraki, Shimomura &amp; Kakui, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BC5396A4E76CF34251F5D7D95FEB826" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AB0C617F235E241990648F63E971A610" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="699601DC65C751E8B2EBB5AB885AE6B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The generic name is a combination of the Greek letter 
<emphasis id="7E2FA3BD56CD5674575A450F895281AA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">delta</emphasis>
(δέλτα), which is triangular in shape, referring to the shape of pleotelson, prefixed to 
<emphasis id="2CDCADE360B2419816A46CEA736322CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">anthura</emphasis>
, from Greek 
<emphasis id="06BF36A894F33D42D42A3E18160FB4EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">anthos</emphasis>
(a flower) and 
<emphasis id="C402C37DDDD8C4BC1343A1849D9EFF04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">oura</emphasis>
(a tail). The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB99722A18B636AE451DB76E08FD6D81" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="24EE6B8E102E22915A2B8FB4CCB479C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BFCD0AB818254F8D56942AAC9CAE5396" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
Like 
<taxonomicName id="B34B4758E40C6236E9D062C5F6D06C6A" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1911" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Pseudanthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7722D68CDF3E8005654B594E0CD68938" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Pseudanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1A66096D9B74DE29F103DF8FB70788B4" authorityName="Bate &amp; Westwood" authorityYear="1866" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Paranthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paranthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="034EF60B56EDDAEC53B34256B3A2E79F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Paranthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D93EDC9359CC52C48A0162B8CF86FB8E" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="41C357270772B2AC5294D3BE92A2B234" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an acute mandible with a 3-articulate palp, but it differs from the former two genera in having pereonite 7 reduced and in lacking pereopods 7. 
<taxonomicName id="C408C98C0288BCD3E47443D14C339CDB" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C0BD79D2E198BDF37BA8F4168A34DB3F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and four paranthurid genera share neotenous characters (reduced pereonite 7 and pereopods 7 lacking), but in 
<taxonomicName id="E05460D46E5667E366B01C261D4703D2" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EFB9EE3438A4BD963C3C297E154BFDAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the mandible is acute, with a 3-articulate palp and maxillipedal endites present, characters that are unique among the neotenous paranthurid genera (Table 
<tableCitation id="43657B0BAAB7B323E3691FE59CE98C2D" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of selected characters among the seven genera in Paranthuridae." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/350764592F578D08F9CF54EE878AC07B" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" tableUuid="350764592F578D08F9CF54EE878AC07B">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="350764592F578D08F9CF54EE878AC07B" ID-Table-UUID="350764592F578D08F9CF54EE878AC07B" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/350764592F578D08F9CF54EE878AC07B" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
