<paragraph id="446714D19BFDF611E506BCA9FE5FD2DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName id="2778B665B8E96F0A92E46A6127EB2325" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1EEA758CED221D4B982CC2A301B2A88" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. does not fit well within the clade (
<taxonomicName id="A1782192D9CDC02D93ADA4587E6B49C9" authorityName="Bate &amp; Westwood" authorityYear="1866" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Paranthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paranthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1F0E9BD2F46239504F5C54338E16007" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Paranthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ neotenous clade) (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="18F21BBDA44BEF179109959A7102B135" author="Poore, GCB" journalOrPublisher="Crustacean Issues" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="63 - 173" refId="B10" refString="Poore, GCB, 2001. Families and genera of Isopoda Anthuridea. Crustacean Issues 13: 63 - 173" title="Families and genera of Isopoda Anthuridea." volume="13" year="2001">Poore 2001</bibRefCitation>
), as it has a maxillipedal endite. Rather, 
<taxonomicName id="D84FCAD48D5F56A202CFA25DDD247732" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D5EDD96F2A54CF5F69F0A935887D8F7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be more closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="ECDC6936EEBD9A1D1E330904E69F34EB" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1911" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Pseudanthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5E557A16295083B7170A1C420D0F007" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Pseudanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as these two share multiple character states such as a triangular pleotelson; elongate triangular, tapering uropodal exopod; and maxillipedal endite. If this latter hypothesis is correct, the neotenous condition in 
<taxonomicName id="0A2FEA80E25203A9FD2D136ACBF5C406" authorityName="Menzies &amp; Glynn" authorityYear="1968" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Paranthuridae</taxonomicName>
may not have had a single origin. In addition to the five neotenous genera now known in 
<taxonomicName id="235BB60B25CA5AE70EAB64158A6EB882" authorityName="Menzies &amp; Glynn" authorityYear="1968" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Paranthuridae</taxonomicName>
, three neotenous genera are known in anthuroid isopods (
<bibRefCitation id="38AE89DBEBBB30B7651A35CAD651D156" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" author="Poore, GCB" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="171 - 180" refId="B11" refString="Poore, GCB, 2009. Leipanthura casuarina, new genus and species of anthurid isopod from Australian coral reefs without a &quot;five-petalled&quot; tail (Isopoda: Cymothoida: Anthuroidea). ZooKeys 18: 171 - 180, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" title="Leipanthura casuarina, new genus and species of anthurid isopod from Australian coral reefs without a &quot; five-petalled &quot; tail (Isopoda: Cymothoida: Anthuroidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" volume="18" year="2009">Poore 2009</bibRefCitation>
): the monotypic genera 
<taxonomicName id="EEFDF1F46299B3B4DEE0C2B34B09392A" authorityName="Kensley" authorityYear="1980" class="Malacostraca" family="Anthuridae" genus="Exallanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Exallanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="200F332E6F4BFFBD81FD72B7087F55C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Exallanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kensley, 1980 and 
<taxonomicName id="178541369A9B3C9E432C9D2D89313855" authorityName="Poore" authorityYear="2009" class="Malacostraca" family="Anthuridae" genus="Leipanthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leipanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23DB5C158BE6579E3F4710E5EC32A88F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Leipanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poore, 2009 in 
<taxonomicName id="F86F723DA57EE9308B67B3EB95468F0B" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" class="Malacostraca" family="Anthuridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anthuridae</taxonomicName>
Leach, 1814; and the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D496C3F426E9097FDC786F8C6B991E2C" authorityName="Kensley" authorityYear="1981" class="Malacostraca" family="Leptanthuridae" genus="Curassanthura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Curassanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9380E216A5703603FB13AAD24FF88D0A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Curassanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kensley, 1981 in 
<taxonomicName id="F87D077C573A01662B7DCBDC6F974B9A" authorityName="Poore" authorityYear="2001" class="Malacostraca" family="Leptanthuridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leptanthuridae</taxonomicName>
Poore, 2001. We note that 
<bibRefCitation id="D3D2662836FE3F20A38EAB410C08AA90" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" author="Poore, GCB" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="171 - 180" refId="B11" refString="Poore, GCB, 2009. Leipanthura casuarina, new genus and species of anthurid isopod from Australian coral reefs without a &quot;five-petalled&quot; tail (Isopoda: Cymothoida: Anthuroidea). ZooKeys 18: 171 - 180, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" title="Leipanthura casuarina, new genus and species of anthurid isopod from Australian coral reefs without a &quot; five-petalled &quot; tail (Isopoda: Cymothoida: Anthuroidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.18.198" volume="18" year="2009">Poore (2009)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the 
<taxonomicName id="75D37A6F50BCF35A93ABBBB959E63DF5" authorityName="Kensley" authorityYear="1980" class="Malacostraca" family="Anthuridae" genus="Exallanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Exallanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5E354B5EF4560568C98CF7DDF9A5798" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Exallanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females 
<emphasis id="1B5D757F314289FFCCAC348B8DBADB4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="90F4287098B9339AC4FE0E07E8956ACB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.304" author="Kensley, B" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 37" refId="B4" refString="Kensley, B, 1980. Anthuridean isopod crustaceans from the International Indian Ocean Expedition, 1960-1965, in the Smithsonian Collections. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 304 (304): 1 - 37, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.304" title="Anthuridean isopod crustaceans from the International Indian Ocean Expedition, 1960 - 1965, in the Smithsonian Collections." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.304" volume="304" year="1980">Kensley (1980)</bibRefCitation>
may actually have been manca individuals.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="313ED6A1A9F2AE3EEA48E06B75D3D37D" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The neotenous species 
<taxonomicName id="D4D4FD8A84F8A4A53AA83DD42495BF1B" authorityName="Kensley &amp; Heard" authorityYear="1991" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Califanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Califanthura minuta" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="F3A741EA052E99E1AD5FF2820297DC2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Califanthura minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kensley &amp; Heard, 1991 from the British West Indies may belong in 
<taxonomicName id="2CB550680505385673A1CFAB6F03210B" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C3DC4328532A7D589D2EB629E8B96F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. It has the triangular pleotelson and tapering uropodal exopod (
<bibRefCitation id="AF8A604B7E8D81CD3822C1FEFED5CE90" DOI="https://doi.org/10.18785/grr.0803.03" author="Kensley, B" journalOrPublisher="Gulf Research Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="237 - 257" refId="B6" refString="Kensley, B, Heard, RW, 1991. Studies on the Crustacea from the Turks and Caicos Islands, British West Indies. I. Four new marine isopod crustaceans from the vicinity of Pine Cay. Gulf Research Reports 8 (3): 237 - 257, DOI: https://doi.org/10.18785/grr.0803.03" title="Studies on the Crustacea from the Turks and Caicos Islands, British West Indies. I. Four new marine isopod crustaceans from the vicinity of Pine Cay." url="https://doi.org/10.18785/grr.0803.03" volume="8" year="1991">Kensley and Heard 1991</bibRefCitation>
) that occur in 
<taxonomicName id="E230EF2C190E54901BF58DCA573ABD84" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="030B86D19DD6ABC0B5297847BD1497EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but not in other 
<taxonomicName id="740FF7BB8E0A4323282643E00A2A936E" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1977" class="Malacostraca" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Califanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Califanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F6FC5F4861C54E925D1620DA08E2E574" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Califanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. However, as the shape of mandible and the presence or absence of the maxillipedal endite (characters diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName id="674B556068A0656BA3CCBC93F306366C" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7A8294E1F413E6F55028CD447BBEFF93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are unknown for 
<taxonomicName id="A95392F7294EE0FBECFF20351A571DF2" genus="C." lsidName="C. minuta" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="560C5D0BB9469383EC015EF36B4E2039" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">C. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we refrain from transferring it to 
<taxonomicName id="9B5C997479D7ABBEEE82E2CF87D4DF0D" authorityName="Shiraki &amp; Shimomura &amp; Kakui" authorityYear="2022" family="Paranthuridae" genus="Deltanthura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltanthura" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ECA21ADAD4C1CD989428E4B4CFD31A15" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Deltanthura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
